==English==
===Noun===
'''railing''' (plural '''railings''')
# A [[fence]] or [[barrier]] consisting of one or more horizontal [[rail]]s and vertical supports.
# A '''hand railing''' is in place to provide guidance on stairs or in corridors.
# A '''guard railing''' is in place to prevent accidental falls from an elevated area.
# During the war, everyone's '''railings''' were taken away to make bombers.
# Note: British use is normally the plural.

